title: For Sale/Trade:  DP51 9mm
postcontent:
I have a dp51 9mm pistol with one magazine for sale or trade, just wanting something different.

Dp51 is the US/civilian version of the South Korean k5 service pistol. It has a "fast action" trigger system! where the hammer can be pushed forward while the mainspring remains cocked. This results in a long but light trigger. The pistol can also function in double action and single action modes, and has an ambidextrous safety.

The magazine holds 13 rounds. The pistol can also use S&W 4900 series magazines, though they will slightly protrude from the bottom of the grip, maybe an 1/8 in or so.

title: For Sale:  Browning A-Bolt 300WSM
postcontent:
This is a sweet gun and i'm not in any pinch to let it go. Just don't really need it and someone else can enjoy it if it's what you're looking for. The A-bolt with the 60% short draw is awesome! The trigger is one of my favorites by far.

A very sophisticated bolt action. 
With a short 60Â° lift, the bolt incorporates a non-rotating bolt sleeve that runs the full length of the bolt. When unlocked, three guide ribs on the bolt sleeve align with the three locking lugs to allow the bolt to slide smoothly. When locked, these three lugs provide massive bolt strength. The A-Bolt feeds very smoothly because of its unique, patented cartridge depressor that stays in position, independent of the bolt rotation, as the bolt slides gently over the cartridges in the magazine. The bolt face is recessed, completely surrounding the cartridge base. A cocking indicator located at the rear of the bolt offers visual and tactile firing pin status.

Barrel
The barrel is free floating and glass bedded at the recoil lug and front of receiver to maintain the proper spacing around the barrel for consistent accuracy. The recessed muzzle crown helps protect the rifling. Barrels are triple checked for interior finish, straightness and air-gauged for uniformity.

Trigger
A chrome-plated trigger sear provides cleaner, crisper trigger pull. Screw adjustable and pre-set at approximately 4 lbs.

Magazine
Hinged floorplate with detachable box magazine makes it simple and fast to load a spare magazine.

Magazine Capacity
For all A-Bolts 300 WSM: Three in magazine, one in chamber.

title: For Sale/Trade:  2003 Saab 9-3 6 Spees Manual ARC
postcontent:
I have a high mileage Saab for sale 367,000 plus miles(I just drove to Cleveland and back). This car still runs great. Exterior color is silver and the interior is gray leather. I bought the car with around 45,000 miles and have owned it ever since. I will start with the bad first. The check engine light is on due to the secondary air injector pump and check valve not working. This is a non issue as this only is emissions equipment that engages on cold starts to add air to the exhaust fumes creating slightly less pollution. This has not worked for the past 100,000 miles and has not effected performance at all. The other problem is the fuel gauge does not work, which has not been an issue if I fill up soon after 400 miles driven on a full tank. Cosmetically the car has some nicks in the paint and a couple small dings. The front fascia is pretty scratched up. The interior is smoke free and is in excellent shape except for the drivers seat has cracked a bit but not torn. Enough with the bad.
Now with the good. The car has many options including heated seats, aux audio input, traction control, moonroof, duel climate control. I have done most of the maintenance over the years and know this car inside and out. I have always used premium fuel and done regular oil changes with Mobil 1 synthetic. For any perspective buyer I can go over in great detail everything that has been done over the years. The tires are Michelin Primacy MXV4 with plenty of tread left. I see no reason why this car can not go another 100,000 miles. I would like to do it myself but I have too many cars right now. If anyone is interested or has questions don't hesitate to ask. I can send some pictures to those who are serious. I really love this car it gets great fuel economy 29-30 mpg average, pulls hard with the turbo and rare 6 speed manual, no rust (car has been in North Carolina) low maintenance if properly cared for, and is comfortable enough for long trips.
